obar Islands","nameIt":"अंडमान और निकोबार द्वीप समूह","capital":"Port Blair","lat":11.7,"lng":92.8,"emoji":"🏝️","colour":"ff4caf50","boundingBox":{"north":13.5,"south":6.8,"east":95,"west":91.8},"placeCount":13,"restaurantCount":14,"bestTimeToVisit":"Visit from November to April for island exploration and water activities.","heroImage":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1640718835374-6116a99c6e6c?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxQb3J0JTIwQmxhaXIlMjBoYXJib3IlMjBjb2xvbmlhbHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzOTY3OTY1fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"ABHISHEK CHAKRABORTY"},"cardImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1640718835374-6116a99c6e6c?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxQb3J0JTIwQmxhaXIlMjBoYXJib3IlMjBjb2xvbmlhbHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzOTY3OTY1fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"},{"id":"ladakh","name":"Ladakh","nameIt":"ལ་དྭགས","capital":"Leh","lat":34,"lng":77.5,"emoji":"⛰️","colour":"ff2196f3","boundingBox":{"north":35.8,"south":32.5,"east":78.6,"west":76.5},"placeCount":9,"restaurantCount":14,"bestTimeToVisit":"Visit from June to September for mountain trekking and monastery visits.","heroImage":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1593118845043-359e5f628214?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxQYW5nb25nJTIwVHNvJTIwbGFrZSUyMExhZGFraHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzOTY3OTk3fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Hans-Jurgen Mager"},"cardImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1593118845043-359e5f628214?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxQYW5nb25nJTIwVHNvJTIwbGFrZSUyMExhZGFraHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzOTY3OTk3fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"}],"top10":[{"rank":1,"name":"Delhi","placeId":"delhi","regionId":"uttar_pradesh","regionName":"Uttar Pradesh","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1587474260584-136574528ed5?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxEZWxoaSUyMEluZGlhfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwMzQ3MjV8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"shalender kumar"},"description":"India's capital and largest metropolitan area, Delhi is the political, cultural, and economic heart of the nation. Visitors flock here for iconic monuments like India Gate and the Red Fort, world-class museums, diverse cuisine, and its role as the primary gateway for international travelers to India."},{"rank":2,"name":"Agra","placeId":"agra_city","regionId":"uttar_pradesh","regionName":"Uttar Pradesh","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1591018653367-9c01498b3320?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxBZ3JhJTIwRm9ydCUyMGdhdGVzJTIwYXJjaGl0ZWN0dXJlfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM5NDc3NTl8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Arun Geetha Viswanathan"},"description":"A historic city on the Yamuna River that served as the capital of the Mughal Empire and home to three UNESCO World Heritage Sites including the Taj Mahal, Agra Fort, and Fatehpur Sikri. Beyond monuments, it offers vibrant bazaars, authentic Mughlai cuisine, and a fascinating blend of medieval and modern Indian culture."},{"rank":3,"name":"Mumbai","placeId":"mumbai","regionId":"maharashtra","regionName":"Maharashtra","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1595658658481-d53d3f999875?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxHYXRld2F5JTIwb2YlMjBJbmRpYSUyME11bWJhaXxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzOTUxNjQxfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Renzo D'souza"},"description":"India's financial capital and Bollywood hub, Mumbai is a vibrant megacity blending colonial architecture with ultra-modern skyscrapers. Must-see landmarks include the Gateway of India, Marine Drive, and the historic Victorian buildings that reflect the city's rich imperial past."},{"rank":4,"name":"Jaipur","placeId":"jaipur","regionId":"rajasthan","regionName":"Rajasthan","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1605601922734-a9c13b0ce8e9?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxKYWlwdXIlMjBwaW5rJTIwY2l0eSUyMHBhbGFjZXxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzOTQ3Nzk3fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Indre Velaviciute"},"description":"The capital of Rajasthan and gateway to the state, Jaipur is famous for its distinctive pink-painted old city, stunning palaces, and vibrant bazaars. The city's geometric grid layout, City Palace, and Jantar Mantar astronomical site make it an essential cultural and architectural destination."},{"rank":5,"name":"Bangalore","placeId":"bangalore","regionId":"karnataka","regionName":"Karnataka","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1687158266872-fd2773fa76c6?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxCYW5nYWxvcmUlMjBjaXR5JTIwc2t5bGluZSUyMElUJTIwcGFya3N8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzk1ODYwNHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Mahadev Ittina"},"description":"India's tech capital and the state capital, Bangalore is a modern metropolis with excellent restaurants, nightlife, and tech parks. It serves as the main hub for exploring Karnataka and offers vibrant culture alongside historical sites like Tipu Sultan's Palace and Bangalore Fort."},{"rank":6,"name":"Goa","placeId":"goa","regionId":"goa","regionName":"Goa","image":null,"description":"India's premier beach destination, Goa is famous for its picturesque beaches, Portuguese colonial heritage, vibrant nightlife, and relaxed atmosphere. Millions of domestic and international tourists visit annually to enjoy water sports, seafood cuisine, spice plantations, and the unique blend of Indian and Portuguese culture."},{"rank":7,"name":"Kochi","placeId":"kochi","regionId":"kerala","regionName":"Kerala","image":null,"description":"Kerala's largest city and a major port with a fascinating blend of Portuguese, Dutch, and British colonial architecture, particularly in the historic Fort Kochi area. The Chinese fishing nets, spice markets, and vibrant arts scene make it an essential gateway to Kerala."},{"rank":8,"name":"Varanasi","placeId":"varanasi_city","regionId":"uttar_pradesh","regionName":"Uttar Pradesh","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1706186839147-0d708602587b?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxWYXJhbmFzaSUyMEdhbmdlcyUyMGdoYXRzJTIwc3VucmlzZXxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzOTQ3NzYxfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Martijn Vonk"},"description":"One of the world's oldest continuously inhabited cities and Hinduism's holiest site, Varanasi sits on the sacred Ganges River where pilgrims come to bathe, pray, and perform ancient rituals. The chaotic maze of narrow lanes, burning ghats, boat rides at dawn, and spiritual energy create an intensely transformative travel experience."},{"rank":9,"name":"Udaipur","placeId":"udaipur","regionId":"rajasthan","regionName":"Rajasthan","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1589901164570-f9de6556e1c1?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxVZGFpcHVyJTIwQ2l0eSUyMFBhbGFjZSUyMExha2UlMjBQaWNob2xhfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM5NDc4MDB8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Pranav Panchal"},"description":"Known as the Venice of Rajasthan, Udaipur is built around stunning lakes and features the magnificent City Palace overlooking Lake Pichola. The romantic lakeside setting, ornate palaces, and artistic heritage make it one of India's most picturesque and visited destinations."},{"rank":10,"name":"Manali","placeId":"manali","regionId":"himachal_pradesh","regionName":"Himachal Pradesh","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1593181629936-11c609b8db9b?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxNYW5hbGklMjBtb3VudGFpbnMlMjBhZHZlbnR1cmV8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzk0NDIwM3ww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Iftekhar Nibir"},"description":"A vibrant adventure hub in the Kullu Valley at 2,050 meters, Manali is famous for trekking, mountaineering, paragliding, and white-water rafting in stunning mountain scenery. The town combines natural beauty with a lively backpacker culture, local temples, and easy access to Rohtang Pass and the Himalayas."}]}